<P><STRONG>FourTextures</STRONG> is sample C++ code illustrating the use =
of=20
multiple textures in OpenGL. &nbsp; It is intended to accompany the book =

<EM><STRONG>3D Computer Graphics: A mathematical approach with =
OpenGL</STRONG>,=20
</EM>by S. Buss, Cambridge University Press, 2003. &nbsp; However, it =
can be=20
used independently as well.</P>
<P><STRONG>FourTextures</STRONG> reads four texture map from a bitmap =
file=20
(<STRONG>.bmp</STRONG> extension).&nbsp;&nbsp; The main program is in=20
<STRONG>TextureMap.cpp. &nbsp; </STRONG>The C++ class =
<STRONG>RgbImage</STRONG>=20
is used to read the images' data from a bitmap files.</P>
